<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03096c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03096c">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03096c"> 96(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> consolatio cibi / (if guest come / on fast)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[On &lsquo;Colmcille and Brethren at Iona&rsquo;]</font> If a visitor happened to arrive on an ordinary fast day of the week, the fast was relaxed in his favor, and a <mark>consolatio cibi</mark> was allowed. <small> Benedict Fitzpatrick, <a name="BFIM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BFIM"><cite title="source">Ireland and the Making of Britain</cite></a> (1922) 134</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
